  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the type of questions which belong to human behavior topic and not to human nature topic?",
  "response": "Human behavior and human nature are related concepts, but they refer to different aspects of human actions and characteristics. Here are examples of questions that typically belong to the topic of human behavior rather than human nature:\n\n1. **Influence of Environment:**\n   - How does social environment impact individual behavior?\n   - What role does peer pressure play in adolescent decision-making?\n\n2. **Behavioral Economics:**\n   - How do cognitive biases affect consumer purchasing decisions?\n   - What factors influence risk-taking behavior in financial investments?\n\n3. **Cultural Influences:**\n   - How do cultural norms affect communication styles among different groups?\n   - In what ways do societal expectations shape gender roles and behaviors?\n\n4. **Psychological Factors:**\n   - How does stress influence human behavior in the workplace?\n   - What impact does childhood trauma have on adult relationships?\n\n5. **Behavioral Modification:**\n   - What techniques are most effective for changing unhealthy habits?\n   - How does positive reinforcement influence learning and behavior in children?\n\n6. **Group Dynamics:**\n   - How does groupthink affect decision-making in teams?\n   - What are the behavioral patterns observed in crowd behavior during emergencies?\n\n7. **Social Identity:**\n   - How does belonging to a particular social group influence individual behavior?\n   - In what ways does identity (e.g., racial, ethnic, religious) shape interpersonal interactions?\n\n8. **Motivation and Goals:**\n   - How do intrinsic and extrinsic motivations affect work performance?\n   - What behavioral strategies can individuals use to achieve personal goals?\n\n9. **Adaptation and Learning:**\n   - How do people adapt their behaviors in response to new social contexts?\n   - What role does observation play in learning behaviors from others?\n\n10. **Mental Health:**\n    - How do mental health conditions influence daily behavior?\n    - In what ways can therapy change maladaptive behaviors?\n\nThese kinds of questions focus on specific actions, influences, and changes in behavior, while questions surrounding human nature would typically address more inherent traits and characteristics common to all humans, such as instincts, drives, and universal tendencies.",
